title: Yreka High tennis and volleyball teams at home today
text: Yreka High tennis and volleyball teams at home today Comment   By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 2:17 PM By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 2:17 PM YREKA The Yreka High volleyball and girls tennis squads are at home today against West Valley. The Lady Miners tennis team is 11-0 in Northern Athletic League play and has already won the NAL crown. They end the regular season on Tuesday looking to go 12-0 in the NAL against the Lady Eagles. The contest begins at 3:30 p.m. at the tennis courts at the high school. The Yreka varsity volleyball team faces West Valley at 6:30 p.m. at the big gym at the high school. Yreka is 14-12 overall and 1-1 in the NAL after defeating Anderson at home last Tuesday and falling to Corning on the road on Thursday. The Lady Eagles come in at 21-3 overall and 2-0 in the NAL. The junior varsity game begins at 5:30 p.m., while the freshman contest has 4:30 p.m. start By Daily News staff   By Daily News staff
